        <body>       
                 
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>New York City<lb/>
                Jan. 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1888.<lb/></p>
            <p>To My Teacher<lb/>
                Rev. Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>My object in writing to you<lb/> is to <sic>deside</sic> the following question.<lb/>  There is a class of Polish Jews in the<lb/> City of New York who claim they know<lb/> more of our Hebrew than any nation<lb/> on the face of the Earth.  I come across<lb/> them frequently and I find them very<lb/> presuming.  I have not yet forgotten<lb/> the instructions I received from you.<lb/>  I mean in Theory&#45;&#45;The practical part<lb/> I have <sic>conquored</sic> since my manhood.<lb/>  The question which I am desirous for you<lb/> to <sic>deside</sic> is this&#58; A Pole who is a constant<lb/> visitor in the &#91;Hebrew&#93; was <sic>aguing</sic> with<lb/> me on the meaning of the word &#91;Hebrew&#93; the way<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>they pronounce the Hebrew is difficult<lb/> for me to understand.  I managed to<lb/> make him understand that &#91;Hebrew&#93; was<lb/> Salt&#95;. he insisted it was not.  I claimed<lb/> that the letters he <sic>written</sic> was wrong&#44; and<lb/> I commenced to write the three letters<lb/> in Hebrew which <sic>surprized</sic> him very much<lb/> to see an Englishman write Hebrew.<lb/>  He will have that &#91;Hebrew&#93; means King.<lb/>  I showed him where his grand mistake<lb/> was and again I <sic>written</sic> &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> means King<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; means Salt.<lb/>  I told him I never saw such a<lb/> word written&#44; and that&#44; if he means<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93; that word signifies &#34;to Reign&#44;<lb/> No&#33; No&#33; he exclaimed &#91;Hebrew&#93; means<lb/> King and is written and punctuated<lb/> that way.<lb/></p>
            <p>I thought it was useless of<lb/> me to try to convince this man as<lb/> he insisted that he was right&#44; and I<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>was wrong therefore I leave the question<lb/> for you to <sic>deside</sic>&#44; and as in my mind<lb/> there is no other <sic>decition</sic> but yours will<lb/> I bow down to&#44; so please answer the<lb/> question<lb/></p>
            <p>My respects to your family<lb/> and wishing you all well<lb/> From Your<lb/> Scholar<lb/> Abraham Saqui<lb/></p>
            <p>Address <del>41</del> 433<lb/> Grant st City N. Y.<lb/> care of Mr S. Kramer.<lb/></p>
            <p>I retain my mental powers yet&#44; the<lb/> following is a proof&#58;<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/> I <sic>written</sic> this in school for you 44 years ago.<lb/></p>
            </body>
